result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
10:16 a.m.  Defendant in custody and present in court with Atty.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by Atty Haase - will be a plea hearing and recites agreement, will plea to counts 3,4,5 & 6 on 2014CF121, with counts 1 & 2, 2014CMa64 & 2015CM26 being dismissed and read-in and count 7 being dismissed and request for presentence investigation.  DA concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty and as domestic.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.  (If felony) Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on counts 3,4,5 & 6 on 2014CF121.  Court orders counts 1 & 2 on 2014CF121, 2015CM26 & 2014CM164 be dismissed and read-in and count 7 on 2014CF121 be dismissed outright.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Court orders a Pre-Sentence investigation be completed and filed with the court within 60 days.  DA confirms compliance with victim witness rights.  Court will set for sentencing in approx 60 days.

Court adjourned at 10:26 a.m.
from Atty Jeffrey Haase dated March 25, 2015 - requests the plea hearing scheduled on 03/31/2015 be rescheduled

2:57 p.m.  Defendant in custody and present in court with Atty Jeffrey Haase.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by Atty Haase - has an agreement on all matters and requests a plea & sentencing be scheduled on another date.  Court will set for plea hearing - March 31, 2015 at 10:30 a.m.

Statement by the Court regarding the NGI plea on 14CF121. Statement by Atty Haase - confims that the defendant withdraws the NGI plea.  Defendant concurs.

Court adjourned at 2:59 p.m.

10:15 a.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Jeffrey Haase.  Lisa Vanden Branden for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by Atty Haase, a few more things to discuss with the DA, and requests matter be set for plea & sentencing.  Court sets for plea & sentencing on March 17, 2015 at 2:45 p.m.

Court adjourned at 10:18 a.m.
Plea hearing on March 3, 2015 at 10:00 am.

9:06 a.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Jeffrey Haase.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty Haase confirms receipt of the criminal complaint and waives reading. Court instructs the defendant of the maximum penalty on each count.  Court finds probable cause.  Atty Haase enters a plea of NOT GUILTY on behalf of the defendant.  DA makes bond recommendation.  Court sets bond at $500.00 signature bond.  

Statement by Atty Haase - an offer has been made and requests a plea be scheduled.  Court will set for Plea Hearing on March 3, 2015 at 10:00 a.m.

Court adjourned at 9:09 a.m.
